The article is a statement by President Obama on the retirement of Senator Harry Reid. The President praises Senator Reid for his fighting spirit and his dedication to fighting for good jobs, a safer environment, and affordable healthcare. The President also highlights Reid's willingness to make tough decisions and stand up to special interests. He acknowledges Reid's commitment to the people of Nevada, as well as his humble background and determination to provide opportunities for everyone. The President considers Reid not only an ally but also a friend and expresses pride in their accomplishments together. He looks forward to continuing to work with Reid and wishes him and his wife well in the future.